<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Document xmlns="http://www.suscopts.org/CopticReader">   <Section>      <Title>         <Language id="English">Response to the Pauline Epistle</Language>         <Language id="Coptic">Pih~mot gar...</Language>      </Title>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                     The response to the Pauline Epistle is chanted:         </Language>      </Comment>            <Text>         <Language id="Coptic">            Pih~mot gar m~Pen[oic I/couc Pi,~rictoc: efe~swpi nem peka~gion p~neuma: pa[oic n~iwt ettai/out n~ar,ie~reuc papa abba (nim)         </Language>         <Language id="English">            The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your saintly spirit, my lord, the honored father, the archpriest, Pope Abba (...).         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">            نعمة ربنا يسوع المسيح تكون مع روحك الطاهرة يا سيدى الأب المكرم رئيس الكهنة البابا أنبا (...)         </Language>               </Text>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                     In the presence of a metropolitan, the following is added.         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">                     وإن كان حاضراً  مطران فيزاد له:         </Language>      </Comment>            <Text>         <Language id="Coptic">            nem peniwt m~m/tropolit/c abba (nim).         </Language>         <Language id="English">            And our father the metropolitan, Abba (...).         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">            وأبانا المطرانَ أنبا (...)         </Language>               </Text>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                     In the presence of a bishop, the following is added.         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">                     وللأسقف يقال:         </Language>      </Comment>            <Text>         <Language id="Coptic">            nem peniwt n~e~pickopoc abba (nim).         </Language>         <Language id="English">            And our father the bishop, Abba (...).         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">            وأبانا الأسقفَ أنبا (...)         </Language>               </Text>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                    In the presence of more than one metropolitan, the following is added.         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">                    وإن كان حاضراً معه مطارنة فيقال:         </Language>      </Comment>            <Text>         <Language id="Coptic">            nem nenio] m~m/tropolit/c n/et,/ neman.         </Language>         <Language id="English">            And our fathers the metropolitans who are with us.         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">            وآباءنا المطارنةَ الكائنين معنا.         </Language>               </Text>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                    In the presence of more than one bishop, the following is added:         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">                    وللأساقفة يقال:         </Language>      </Comment>            <Text>         <Language id="Coptic">            nem nenio] n~e~pickopoc  n/et,/ neman.         </Language>         <Language id="English">                           And our fathers the bishops who are with us.         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">            وآباءنا الأساقفةَ الكائنين معنا.         </Language>               </Text>            <Comment>         <Language id="English">                     The foregoing is concluded with:         </Language>         <Language id="Arabic">                     وبعد أية جملة من الجمل السابقة يكمل قائلاً:         </Language>      </Comment>            <InsertDocument path="include/MayTheClergy"/>   </Section></Document>